<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aaron Rodgers said he had an 'increased love of life' and was 'in a lot better head space' Tuesday during an interview following his recent split from Danica Patrick.</p>

<p>The 36-year-old football star opened up while on The Pat McAfee Show after a caller asked why he appeared 'rejuvenated' during the 2020 football season.</p>

<p>'I have just a new and increased love of life and I have made decisions and changes and habits that put me in a lot better head space,' Aaron responded.</p>

<p>Loving life: Aaron Rodgers said he had an 'increased love of life' and was 'in a lot better head space Tuesday during a radio interview following his recent split from Danica Patrick</p>

<p>'There's just a lot of things that have come together in my life over the last few months that have really been enjoyable and reminded me, given me perspective, on life and in football to view things through the most positive lens that I possibly can,' Aaron added.</p>

<p>The Green Bay Packers quarterback added: 'That's why I'm having so much fun, and it starts with love. And then surround yourself with people that you really enjoy'.</p>

<p>Aaron even cited his weekly participation on The Pat McAfee Show as an example of his new outlook because of his 'love' for show collaborator, friend and former teammate AJ Hawk and respect for Pat.</p>

<p>He said that he looks forward to joining the show each week and called it 'another step' in the process of self-growth.</p>

<p>Former couple: Danica and Aaron, shown in July 2018 in Santa Monica, California, split up in July</p>

<p>Weekly participation: Aaron even cited his weekly participation on The Pat McAfee Show as an example of his new outlook because of his 'love' for show collaborator, friend and former teammate AJ Hawk and respect for Pat</p>

<p>Strong start: The Green Bay Packers quarterback is shown scrambling Sunday in Green Bay, Wisconsin as his team improved to 2-0 with a win over the Detroit Lions</p>

<p>'It's mindfulness and positivity and love and kindness and integrity. Just putting it all together, I think for me, has made me a lot happier and I'm just enjoying football and enjoying life a lot more,' he said.</p>

<p>Aaron and Danica, 38, met at the ESPY Awards in 2012 and started dating in 2018.</p>

<p>The former pro race car driver confirmed in July through a representative that they were 'no longer together' after dating for more than two years.</p>

<p>Happier times: Danica posted a sweet birthday last December for Aaron on Instagram</p>

<p>Aaron previously dated actress Olivia Munn, 40, from 2014 to 2017.</p>

<p>The Chico, California native won Super Bowl XLV in February 2011 with the Packers and was named Most Valuable Player in the win over the Pittsburgh Steelers.</p>

<p>Aaron and the Packers have started the 2020 season with two straight wins.</p>

<p>Ex girlfriend: Aaron previously dated actress Olivia Munn, 40, from 2014 to 2017 and they are shown in February 2015 in Beverly Hills, California</p>
